    author,
    date: "May 5, 2021",
    readTime: "3 min read",
    content: "Divorce is often an overwhelming process that is filled with emotions, petitions, and settlements. While nobody ever wishes to get to the point of divorce, it is a hard pill that the parties have to swallow. There are often many issues to be settled in one suite, such as outlined by Bloodworth Lawfirm, such as paternity, child support, child custody, or the division of wealth and debt. Without proper eyes from an experienced divorce attorney, it is possible to get a raw deal.\n### Help in Drafting and Reviewing a Divorce Agreement\nNot all divorce settlements have to be messy and take place before a court. It is common to agree to the uncontested divorce or have the lawyer find alternative means of dispute resolution to ensure that both parties are satisfied. It is common for the agreements in the divorce settlement to be written in jargon that only a lawyer can understand advice. A divorce lawyer is there to help you go through the fine print and ensure you get the best deal in the settlement. A lawyer is important as they understand all the aspects of divorce and advise you to keep you from losing out in an agreement.\n### Help the Client Stay Within the Law\nYour lawyer has to help you during the divorce proceeding from committing crimes and felonies that would make the divorce difficult. Fueled by revenge, there are times when one of the spouses may try to gather fictitious evidence, especially in a child custody case. Such acts are illegal and could backfire on the client if they have no idea. A lawyer advises the client on all the legal channels to use the best results.\n### Educate the Client on the Proceedings and Law\nA client should promptly be briefed on the case and possible solutions to make the right choice. Before you even file your divorce papers or are after you are served divorce papers, it is important to settle down with your lawyer to understand what the law can allow you to get in the divorce settlement. It is good for the lawyer to tell the client what they are supposed to expect in alimony, child support, and child custody. The lawyer should furnish the client with all the necessary information to win the case or reach the most favorable outcome. Clients should be acquainted with what to discuss with the lawyer on the first meeting from DivorceNet to distinguish if the divorce lawyer is suitable.\n\nOriginal source: https://bengulish.wordpress.com/2021/05/05/3-reasons-to-hire-a-divorce-lawyer/",
